<title>NETHERLANDS: UNILEVER SELLS MICROBIOLOGY OPS.</title>
<headline>UNILEVER SELLS MICROBIOLOGY OPS.</headline>
<dateline>ROTTERDAM 1997-01-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Unilever NV/Plc said it sold the professional microbiology business of its Unipath subsidiary to British venture capital company Cinven for an undisclosed sum.  </p>
<p>Cinven's total funding for the acquisition is 250 million guilders, including banking facilities for working capital and future expension, Unilever said in a statement.</p>
<p>The business - renamed Oxoid Limited and based in Basingstoke - manufactures and markets culture media, and raw materials to make up such media, under the Oxoid brand name.</p>
<p>The business has sales of around 175 million guilders and is consistently profitable, Unilever said.  </p>
<p>The sale results from Unilever's decision to concentrate on Unipath's consumer goods activities which are based in Bedford and which include the Clearblue home testing kits and the recently launched Persona personal system of contraception. </p>
<p>-- Amsterdam +31 20 504 5000</p>
